package org.drools.generated;

declare EmailAddress
    email : String
    valid : boolean
end

rule "Validate Email Address"
when
    $e : EmailAddress(email contains "@", valid == false)
then
    modify($e) { setValid(true) }
end

This DRL code defines a rule that checks if the `email` field of an `EmailAddress` fact contains the "@" symbol. If it does, and the `valid` field is initially `false`, the rule sets the `valid` field to `true`. The rule uses pattern matching with constraints to ensure only emails containing "@" are marked as valid.